-----Account Management Tests:------

--Change name test--

1. Open my.hideez.com in browser
2. Enter clementine.letto@gmail.com in field "Login"
3. Enter 17uipAeRw in field "Login"
4. Click "Log in" button
5. Click on "Account Management" tab
6. Find changing name form
7. Enter Alice in first field
8. Enter Letto in second field
9. Click "Save" button

Expected result:
Greetings message changed on "Hello, new_firstname new_lastname"

--Change password test--

1. Open my.hideez.com in browser
2. Enter clementine.letto@gmail.com in field "Login"
3. Enter 17uipAeRw in field "Login"
4. Click "Log in" button
5. Click on "Account Management" tab
6. Find password changing form
7. Enter 17uipAeRw in field "Old password"
8. Enter 17uipAeRw17uipAeRw in field "New Password"
9. Enter 17uipAeRw17uipAeRw in field "Confirm new password"
10. Click "Change password"

Expected result:
"Your password has been changed" message appeared

-----Add New User Test-----

--Invite new user--

1. Open my.hideez.com in browser
2. Enter clementine.letto@gmail.com in field "Login"
3. Enter 17uipAeRw in field "Login"
4. Click "Log in" button
5. Click on "Default Group - Management system" button
6. Click "Users"
7. Click "Add button"
8. Enter test.user@gmail.com
9. Click "Invite"

Expected result:
User appeared in list of all users and message, that this user invited, appeared

--Confirm Email of new user--
1. Open my.hideez.com in browser
2. Enter clementine.letto@gmail.com in field "Login"
3. Enter 17uipAeRw in field "Login"
5. Click on "Default Group - Management system" button
6. Click "Users"
7. Enter test.user@gmail.com in search field
8. Click search button
9. Click on test.user@gmail.com user
10. In opened tab click "Confirm email"

Expected result:
Button "confirm email" will disapear

-----Give user an admin role-----

1. Open my.hideez.com in browser
2. Enter clementine.letto@gmail.com in field "Login"
3. Enter 17uipAeRw in field "Login"
4. Click "Log in" button
5. Click on "Default Group - Management system" button
6. Click "Users"
7. Enter test.user@gmail.com in search field
8. Click search button
9. Click on test.user@gmail.com user
10. Click on "Roles" tab
11. Click on Admin Role switcher

Expected result: 
Admin role switcher is green colored and message appeared, test.user@gmail.com user will see Default Group Management System button

